public class PoiWorkbookFactory extends WorkbookFactory<PoiWorkbook>

      public PoiWorkbook createStreaming()
      Description copied from class: WorkbookFactory

    • createXls

    • createXlsx

      public PoiWorkbook createXlsx()
      Creates a new empty workbook in XLSX format (Excel 2007+). This is the recommended format for new workbooks as it supports larger datasets and more features than XLS format.
      Returns:
      a new empty workbook in XLSX format
      See Also:
      • createXls()
      • createXlsxStreaming()

    • createXlsxStreaming

      public PoiWorkbook createXlsxStreaming()
      Creates a new empty workbook in XLSX format optimized for streaming operations. This mode is recommended for handling large datasets as it uses minimal memory, but note that it's write-only and some features may be limited.
      Returns:
      a new empty workbook in XLSX format configured for streaming
      See Also:
      • createXlsx()
      • createXls()

    • open

      public PoiWorkbook open(URI uri, com.dua3.utility.options.Arguments importSettings) throws IOException
      Opens an existing workbook from the specified URI with custom import settings. The workbook format (XLS or XLSX) is automatically detected. This method provides additional control over the import process through the importSettings parameter.
      Specified by:
      open in class WorkbookFactory<PoiWorkbook>
      Parameters:
      uri - the URI of the workbook to open
      importSettings - configuration options for the import process, such as character encoding for CSV files or other format-specific settings
      Returns:
      the opened workbook
      Throws:
      IOException - if an I/O error occurs while reading the file
      FileFormatException - if the file format is invalid or the file is corrupted
      See Also:
      • open(URI)
